nts"}],"body":[{"tagName":"p","source":"Drug development is sometimes described as a pipeline, with compounds moving from early laboratory development to laboratory and animal testing to clinical trials in people."},{"tagName":"p","source":"It can take a \u003ca href=\"http://phrma-docs.phrma.org/sites/default/files/pdf/rd_brochure_022307.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003edecade or more\u003c/a\u003e for a new compound to go from initial discovery to the marketplace. Many compounds never even make it that far."},{"tagName":"p","source":"That\u0026rsquo;s why many medications being eyed as potential treatments for COVID-19 are \u003ca href=\"https://www.pharmacytimes.com/news/potential-pipeline-medications-for-the-coronavirus\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003edrugs that already exist\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"In a recent \u003ca href=\"https://bpspubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/bph.15094\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003ereview\u003c/a\u003e in the British Journal of Pharmacology, scientists from the United Kingdom called for wider screening of existing drugs to see if they might work against the coronavirus."},{"tagName":"p","source":"They identified three stages of infection at which the coronavirus could be targeted: keeping the virus from entering our cells, preventing it from replicating inside the cells, and minimizing the damage that the virus does to the organs."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Many of the drugs being developed or tested for COVID-19 are antivirals. These would target the virus in people who already have an infection. "},{"tagName":"p","source":"Lee says antivirals work better if you administer them sooner, \u0026ldquo;before the virus has a chance to multiply significantly.\u0026rdquo; And also before the virus has caused significant \u003ca href=\"/health-news/heres-what-happens-to-the-body-after-contracting-the-coronavirus\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003edamage to the body\u003c/a\u003e, such as to the lungs or other tissues."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.nymc.edu/school-of-health-sciences-and-practice-shsp/shsp-dean/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003eDr. Robert Amler\u003c/a\u003e, dean of the School of Health Sciences and Practice at New York Medical College and a former chief medical officer at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) Agency for Toxic Substances and Disease Registry (ATSDR), says both antivirals and vaccines will be valuable tools in combating COVID-19."},{"tagName":"p","source":"However, he told Healthline that \u0026ldquo;antivirals are likely to be developed and approved before a vaccine, which typically takes longer.\u0026rdquo;"}]},{"id":"Antivirals","header":[{"tagName":"strong","source":"Antivirals"}],"body":[{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003cstrong\u003eRemdesivir\u003c/strong\u003e"},{"tagName":"p","source":"Developed a \u003ca href=\"https://www.statnews.com/2020/03/16/remdesivir-surges-ahead-against-coronavirus/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003edecade\u003c/a\u003e ago, this drug failed in clinical trials against Ebola in 2014. But it was found to be generally safe in people. \u003ca href=\"https://www.jbc.org/content/early/2020/02/24/jbc.AC120.013056\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003eResearch\u003c/a\u003e with MERS showed that the drug blocked the virus from replicating."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The drug is being tested in many \u003ca href=\"https://clinicaltrials.gov/ct2/results?cond=COVID-19\u0026term=remdesivir\u0026cntry=\u0026state=\u0026city=\u0026dist=\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003eCOVID-19 clinical trials\u003c/a\u003e around the world. This includes studies in which remdesivir is being administered alongside other drugs, such as the \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"National Institutes of Health \" rationale=\"Governmental authority\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.nih.gov/news-events/news-releases/nih-clinical-trial-testing-antiviral-remdesivir-plus-anti-inflammatory-drug-baricitinib-covid-19-begins\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003eanti-inflammatory drug baricitinib\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"In late April, the drug\u0026rsquo;s manufacturer Gilead Sciences \u003ca href=\"https://www.cnn.com/2020/04/23/health/remdesivir-trial-gilead-premature/index.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003eannounced\u003c/a\u003e one of its trials had been \u0026ldquo;terminated\u0026rdquo; due to low enrollment. Gilead officials said the results of that trial had been \u0026ldquo;inconclusive\u0026rdquo; when it was ended."},{"tagName":"p","source":"A few days later, the company \u003ca href=\"https://www.usnews.com/news/health-news/articles/2020-04-29/gilead-sciences-says-potential-coronavirus-treatment-remdesivir-shows-promise-in-study\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003eannounced\u003c/a\u003e that preliminary data from another trial of remdesivir overseen by the National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases (NIAID) had \u0026ldquo;met its primary endpoint.\u0026rdquo;"},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003chl-trusted-source source=\"National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases \" rationale=\"Governmental authority\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.niaid.nih.gov/about/director\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003eDr. Anthony Fauci\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e, the institute\u0026rsquo;s director, \u003ca href=\"https://ww