Name":"p","source":"\u003cstrong\u003eHydroxychloroquine and chloroquine\u003c/strong\u003e"},{"tagName":"p","source":"These drugs received emergency use authorization from the FDA at the end of March. At that time, manufacturer Novartis \u003ca href=\"https://www.hhs.gov/about/news/2020/03/29/hhs-accepts-donations-of-medicine-to-strategic-national-stockpile-as-possible-treatments-for-covid-19-patients.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003edonated\u003c/a\u003e about 30 million doses of hydroxychloroquine and one million doses of chloroquine to the nation\u0026rsquo;s Strategic National Stockpile."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Clinical results, though, have been, at best, \u003ca href=\"/health-news/too-early-to-know-if-hydroxychloroquine-will-work\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003emixed\u003c/a\u003e. "},{"tagName":"p","source":"In late May, the World Health Organization \u003ca href=\"https://www.npr.org/sections/coronavirus-live-updates/2020/05/25/861913688/who-halts-hydroxychloroquine-trial-over-safety-concerns\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003eannounced \u003c/a\u003eit was halting its clinical trials of hydroxychloroquine due to safety concerns."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The decision came a few days after researchers \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"The Lancet\" rationale=\"Highly respected journal,Expert written journal,Peer reviewed journal\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(20)31180-6/fulltext\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003ereported \u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003ein The Lancet that patients receiving hydroxychloroquine or chloroquine were dying at higher rates than patients with COVID-19 who weren\u0026rsquo;t given those drugs."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Around the same time, officials in France, Belgium, and Italy \u003ca href=\"https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-hydroxychloroquine/france-bans-hydroxychloroquine-to-treat-covid-19-amid-safety-concerns-idUSKBN233197?il=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003estopped the use\u003c/a\u003e of hydroxycholoroquine for COVID-19 treatment due to safety concerns."},{"tagName":"p","source":"In early May, the authors of an observational study in the New England Journal of Medicine \u003ca href=\"https://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJMoa2012410\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003ereported\u003c/a\u003e that patients who had been given hydroxychloroquine didn\u0026rsquo;t benefit. The medication didn\u0026rsquo;t harm the participants who took it, but the drug also didn\u0026rsquo;t lessen their need for ventilators or reduce their risk of death."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Another \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"JAMA\" rationale=\"Highly respected journal,Expert written journal,Peer reviewed journal\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jama/fullarticle/2766117\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003estudy\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e in JAMA published in May also found that hydroxychloroquine, with or without the antibiotic azithromycin, didn\u0026rsquo;t help people with COVID-19."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Given the scarcity of good data, the authors of an \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"Annals of Internal Medicine\" rationale=\"Highly respected journal,Expert written journal,Peer reviewed journal\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://annals.org/aim/fullarticle/2764065/rush-judgment-rapid-reporting-dissemination-results-its-consequences-regarding-use\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-5r4717\"\u003eopinion piece\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e in the journal Annals of Internal Medicine questioned the use of 